{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddd367423-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s4637"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4637"},"text":"§ 4637.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Notice after separation from service","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The resignation, termination of employment or participation, or separation of an entity-affiliated party shall not affect the jurisdiction and authority of the Director to issue any notice and proceed under this subchapter against any such entity-affiliated party, if such notice is served before the end of the 6-year period beginning on the date such entity-affiliated party ceases to be associated with the regulated entity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddd367424-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/550/tXIII/s1379"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–550, title XIII, § 1379","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 1377, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/3992"},"text":"106 Stat. 3992","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 1379 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/dA/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, div. A, title I","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1153(a)(1), 1156(b)(1), 1157, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-07-30"},"text":"July 30, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/2770"},"text":"122 Stat. 2770","children":[],"tail":", 2777.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddd367425-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddd367426-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"iddd367427-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/550/s1379"},"text":"section 1379 of Pub. L. 102–550","children":[],"tail":" was renumbered section 1379B and is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s4639"},"text":"section 4639 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddd367428-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1157/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1157(4)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “regulated entity.” for “enterprise.” could not be executed because of the prior amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1156/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1156(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":". See below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1157/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1157(3)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “entity-affiliated party” for “director or officer” wherever appearing, was executed by making the substitution for “director or executive officer” in two places, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1157/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1157(2)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “an entity-affiliated party” for “a director or executive officer of an enterprise”, was executed by making the substitution for “a director or executive officer of a regulated entity”, to reflect the probable intent of Congress and the prior amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1156/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1156(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":". See below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1157/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1157(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “6-year” for “2-year”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1156/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1156(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a regulated entity” for “an enterprise” and “the regulated entity” for “the enterprise”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
